âœ… STEP-BY-STEP GUIDE: Flutter Localization (Hindi + English)
ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Add required packages
In your pubspec.yaml:

yaml
Copy
Edit
dependencies:
  flutter:
    sdk: flutter
  flutter_localizations:
    sdk: flutter
  intl: ^0.18.0
Then run:

bash
Copy
Edit
flutter pub get
ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Create your ARB translation files
In this folder:

bash
Copy
Edit
lib/core/appLocalization/
Create:

app_en.arb
json
Copy
Edit
{
  "@@locale": "en",
  "homeScreenTitle": "Your Expense"
}
app_hi.arb
json
Copy
Edit
{
  "@@locale": "hi",
  "homeScreenTitle": "à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¤¾ à¤–à¤°à¥à¤š"
}
You can add more keys similarly.

ğŸ”¹ Step 3: Create a l10n.yaml file in root (next to pubspec.yaml)
yaml
Copy
Edit
arb-dir: lib/core/appLocalization
template-arb-file: app_en.arb
output-localization-file: app_localizations.dart
output-class: AppLocalizations
preferred-supported-locales:
  - en
  - hi
âœ… This file tells Flutter how to generate the localization code.

ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Update pubspec.yaml to enable code generation
Under flutter:, add:

yaml
Copy
Edit
flutter:
  uses-material-design: true
  generate: true
âœ… Do not add localizations: inside flutter: in Flutter 3.8.1.

ğŸ”¹ Step 5: Generate localization code
In terminal, run:

bash
Copy
Edit
flutter gen-l10n
â¡ï¸ This generates app_localizations.dart inside:

bash
Copy
Edit
.dart_tool/flutter_gen/gen_l10n/
ğŸ”¹ Step 6: Import localization in your main.dart
dart
Copy
Edit
import 'package:flutter_localizations/flutter_localizations.dart';
import 'package:flutter_gen/gen_l10n/app_localizations.dart';
ğŸ”¹ Step 7: Add localization setup in MaterialApp
In your main.dart or MyApp widget:

dart
Copy
Edit
MaterialApp(
  locale: Locale('en'), // or dynamically use from provider
  supportedLocales: const [
    Locale('en'),
    Locale('hi'),
  ],
  localizationsDelegates: const [
    AppLocalizations.delegate,
    GlobalMaterialLocalizations.delegate,
    GlobalWidgetsLocalizations.delegate,
    GlobalCupertinoLocalizations.delegate,
  ],
  home: MyHomePage(),
);
ğŸ”¹ Step 8: Use translated strings
In your widgets:

dart
Copy
Edit
Text(AppLocalizations.of(context)!.homeScreenTitle)
ğŸ”¹ Step 9: Add dynamic language switching (optional)
You already created LanguageChangeController. Just make sure:

locale: in MaterialApp reads from Provider

Your button toggles the bool isEnglish and calls notifyListeners()

âœ… Optional Commands
Command	Purpose
flutter pub get	Install packages
flutter pub run build_runner clean	Clean generated files
flutter gen-l10n	Generate localization files
flutter clean && flutter pub get	Full clean install